#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Aṭṭhasatapariyāyavagga"
msgstr "3. The Explanation of the Hundred and Eight"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Pubbasutta → pubbesuttaṃ (bj) | pubbeñāṇaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Pubbasutta"
msgstr "24. Before"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.24:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on "
"awakening—I thought:"

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.2"
msgid ""
"‘katamā nu kho vedanā, katamo vedanāsamudayo, katamā vedanāsamudayagāminī "
"paṭipadā, katamo vedanānirodho, katamā vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr ""
"‘What is feeling? What’s the origin of feeling? What’s the practice that "
"leads to the origin of feeling? What’s the cessation of feeling? What’s the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of feeling?"

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.3"
msgid "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti?"
msgstr "And what is feeling’s gratification, drawback, and escape?’"

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.5"
msgid "‘tisso imā vedanā—"
msgstr "‘There are these three feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.6"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.7"
msgid "Imā vuccanti vedanā."
msgstr "These are called feeling."

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.8"
msgid "Phassasamudayā vedanāsamudayo."
msgstr "Feeling originates from contact."

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.9"
msgid "Taṇhā vedanāsamudayagāminī paṭipadā … pe …"
msgstr "Craving is the practice that leads to the origin of feeling …"

msgctxt "sn36.24:1.10"
msgid ""
"yo vedanāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ. Idaṃ vedanāya "
"nissaraṇan’”ti."
msgstr ""
"Removing and giving up desire and greed for feeling: this is its escape.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.24:1.11"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
